\\\"package.json\\\")                |                     |                  |\\n| View all files                                                                         |                                                                                        |                     |                  |\\n\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n* README\\n\\n# OEBB-API (BB-API)\\n\\nA collection of functions fore node.js to acess train shedules, arrivals/departures, station search and ticketinformation from the OEBB(BB)\\n\\nI had a lot of help help from these great ressources\\n\\n* HAFAS Fahrplanauskunft API - Sammlung\\n* Austrian Federal Railways (BB) API client by juliuste\\n\\nand a documentation file I found on the web\\n\\n## Installation\\n\\nnpm --save install oebb-api\\n\\n## Functions\\n\\n* searchStationsNew\\n* searchStations\\n* getJourneys\\n* getStationBoardData\\n* getStationBoardDataOptions\\n* getStationSearchOptions\\n\\n### searchStationsNew(name)\\n\\nIt returns an promise that resolves to an array of possible stations matching `name`\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n\\noebb.searchStationsNew(\\\"Wien\\\").then(console.log);\\n\\nreturns\\n\\n[{ number: 1190100,\\n    longitude: 16372134,\\n    latitude: 48208547,\\n    name: '''',\\n    meta: ''Wien'' },\\n  { number: 1290401,\\n    longitude: 16375326,\\n    latitude: 48185507,\\n    name: ''Wien Hbf (U)'',\\n    meta: '''' },\\n...\\n...\\n...]\\n\\n### searchStations(options)\\n\\n_searchStation_ is very similar to _searchStationsNew_ it however can take more options and returns more information. You can call getStationSearchOptions to get a prefilled options object.\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n\\nvar options = oebb.getStationSearchOptions();\\noptions.S=\\\"wien h\\\";\\noebb.searchStations(options).then(console.log);\\n\\nIt returns an array with matching stations, POIs, etc.\\n\\n[ { value: ''Wien Hbf (U)'',\\n    id: ''A=1@O=Wien Hbf (U)@X=16375326@Y=48185507@U=181@L=001290401@B=1@p=1513853468@'',\\n    extId: ''001290401'',\\n    type: ''1'',\\n    typeStr: ''[Bhf/Hst]'',\\n    xcoord: ''16375326'',\\n    ycoord: ''48185507'',\\n    state: ''id'',\\n    prodClass: ''6013'',\\n    weight: ''32767'' },\\n  { value: ''Wien Meidling'',\\n    id: ''A=1@O=Wien Meidling@X=16333211@Y=48174559@U=181@L=001191201@B=1@p=1513853468@'',\\n    extId: ''001191201'',\\n    type: ''1'',\\n    typeStr: ''[Bhf/Hst]'',\\n    xcoord: ''16333211'',\\n    ycoord: ''48174559'',\\n    state: ''id'',\\n    prodClass: ''4989'',\\n    weight: ''32588'' },\\n...\\n...\\n...]\\n\\n| Name      | description                                                                                     |\\n| --------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| value:    | name of the station                                                                             |\\n| id        | no idea                                                                                         |\\n| extId     | used in other queries; same as number (not quite shure if the really are the same all the time) |\\n| type      | int representing the type                                                                       |\\n| typeStr   | the type as string                                                                              |\\n| xcoord    | longitude                                                                                       |\\n| ycoord    | latitude                                                                                        |\\n| state     | no idea                                                                                         |\\n| prodClass | no idea                                                                                         |\\n| weight    | I am guessing it represents how close a match the station is to the string                      |\\n\\n### getStationSearchOptions()\\n\\nIt returns an object containing the options for searchStations\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n\\nvar options = oebb.getStationSearchOptions();\\n\\n#### options\\n\\n| Name                | default value | value                     | description                                                    |\\n| ------------------- | ------------- | ------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| REQ0JourneyStopsS0A | 1             | An int between 1 and 255. | It selects the type of station to return e.g. 1 is \\\\[Bhf/Hst\\\\] |\\n| REQ0JourneyStopsB   | 12            | An int greater 0          | the amount of results which are returned                       |\\n| S                   | a string      | the string to match       |                                                                |\\n| js                  | true          | boolean                   | no idea what it does                                           |\\n\\n### getStationBoardData(options)\\n\\nIt returns a promise resolving to an object containing arrival or depature information for a specific station. You can get a prefilled options object, by calling getStationBoardDataOptions\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n\\nvar options = oebb.getStationBoardDataOptions();\\noptions.evaId=1191601;//Ottakring (Wien)\\noebb.getStationBoardData(options).then(console.log);\\n\\nreturns:\\n\\n{ headTexts:\\n   [ ''Zeit'',\\n     ''Fahrt'',\\n     ''Nach'',\\n     ''Steig'',\\n     ''Abfahrten'',\\n     ''Aktuell'',\\n     ''Ankunft'' ],\\n  stationName: ''Ottakring (Wien)'',\\n  stationEvaId: ''1191601'',\\n  boardType: ''dep'',\\n  imgPath: ''/img/'',\\n  iconProductsSubPath: ''vs_oebb/'',\\n  rtInfo: true,\\n  journey:\\n   [ { id: ''875171810'',\\n       ti: ''19:46'',\\n       da: ''23.12.2017'',\\n       pr: ''U3'',\\n       st: ''Wien Simmering'',\\n       lastStop: ''Wien Simmering Bahnhof (U3)'',\\n       ati: ''20:12'',\\n       tr: ''1'',\\n       trChg: false,\\n       rt: false,\\n       rta: false },\\n     { id: ''836641815'',\\n       ti: ''19:46'',\\n       da: ''23.12.2017'',\\n       pr: ''Tram 46'',\\n       st: ''Wien Ring/Volkstheater U'',\\n       lastStop: ''Wien Dr.-K.-Renner-Ring/Volkstheater (Schleife)'',\\n       ati: ''20:00'',\\n       tr: '''',\\n       trChg: ,\\n       rt: { status: null, dlm: ''2'', dlt: ''19:47'' , dld:''23.12.2017''},\\n       rta: false },\\n       ...\\n       ...\\n       ...\\n ],\\n  maxJ: 18 }\\n\\n#### element description\\n\\n##### general:\\n\\n| Name                | description                            |\\n| ------------------- | -------------------------------------- |\\n| headTexts           | headings for arrivals depatures screen |\\n| stationName         | name of station                        |\\n| stationEvaId        | Id of station                          |\\n| boardType           | depatures or arrivals (dep/arr)        |\\n| imgPath             | ?                                      |\\n| iconProductsSubPath | ?                                      |\\n| rtInfo              | ?                                      |\\n| maxJ                | number of returned entries -1          |\\n\\n##### journey:\\n\\n| Name     | description                                                                                   |\\n| -------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| id       | ?                                                                                             |\\n| ti       | arrvial/depature time                                                                         |\\n| da       | arrival/depature date                                                                         |\\n| pr       | name of transport                                                                             |\\n| st       | ?                                                                                             |\\n| lastStop | last stop                                                                                     |\\n| ati      | wehn arrivals depature time from first stop ; when depatures expected time to reach last stop |\\n| tr       | track identifier                                                                              |\\n| trChg    | did the track change                                                                          |\\n\\n##### rt :\\n\\nit describes the delay or other status if there is one. If there is one it contains an object formated as follows:\\n\\n| Name   | description                           |\\n| ------ | ------------------------------------- |\\n| status | current status; \\\"Ausfall\\\" if canceled |\\n| dlm    | how many minutes too late             |\\n| dlt    | actual arrival time                   |\\n| dld    | actual arrival date                   |\\n\\n##### rta\\n\\nit is very similar to rt I think it describes the delay for the arrival, but I am not certain.\\n\\n| Name   | description                                                                          |\\n| ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\\n| status | current status \\\"Ausfall\\\" if canceled then rt too is canceld and rt.status= \\\"Ausfall\\\" |\\n| dlm    | never seen it other than empty                                                       |\\n| dlt    | never seen it other than empty                                                       |\\n\\n### getStationBoardDataOptions()\\n\\nreturns prefilled options for getStationBoardData\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n\\nvar options = oebb.getStationBoardDataOptions();\\n\\n#### options\\n\\n| Name           | default value             | values                    | description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |\\n| -------------- | ------------------------- | ------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| L              | vs\\\\_scotty.vs\\\\_liveticker | vs\\\\_scotty.vs\\\\_liveticker | ?                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |\\n| evaId          | empty                     | integer                   | Id of station; extId or number from [searchStationsNew](#searchstationsnewname) or [searchStations](#searchstationsoptions)                                                                                                                                     |\\n| dirInput       | empty                     | integer                   | Id of Station in which transportation is heading; extId or number f from [searchStationsNew](#searchstationsnewname) or [searchStations](#searchstationsoptions). If it is set only trains which actually stop at the station specified with dirInput are shown |\\n| boardType      | dep                       | dep/arr                   | depatures or arrivals                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           |\\n| time           | current time              | HH:MM                     | time from when to start looking                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |\\n| productsFilter | 1111111111111111          | binary flags?             | selects modes of transportation see [below](#productsfilter) for more information                                                                                                                                                                               |\\n| additionalTime | 0                         | integer                   | in minute. Is added to time                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |\\n| maxJourneys    | 19                        | integer                   | max of returned stations                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |\\n| outputMode     | tickerDataOnly            | tickerDataOnly            | ?                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |\\n| start          | yes                       | yes/no                    | wheter to start query                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           |\\n| selectDate     | period                    | period/tody               | selects mode; if tody dateBegin and dateEnd are ignored.                                                                                                                                                                                                        |\\n| dateBegin      | current date              | String dd.mm.YYYY         | start day for lookup ignored if selectDate=today                                                                                                                                                                                                                |\\n| dateEnd        | current date              | String dd.mm.YYYY         | end date for lookup ignored if selectDate=today                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |\\n\\n##### productsFilter\\n\\nslects which modes of transports should be listed forexample if I set `productsFilter` to 0000110000000000 only s-bahn and regionalzge are shown\\n\\n| Flag number | mode of transport                    |\\n| ----------- | ------------------------------------ |\\n| 1           | railjet                              |\\n| 2           | ?                                    |\\n| 3           | ec and ice                           |\\n| 4           | nightjet d probably also nightjet en |\\n| 5           | regionalzge                         |\\n| 6           | s-bahn                               |\\n| 7           | Bus                                  |\\n| 8           | ?                                    |\\n| 9           | subway                               |\\n| 10          | tram                                 |\\n| 11          | ?                                    |\\n| 12          | ?                                    |\\n| 13          | Westbahn                             |\\n| 14          | ?                                    |\\n| 15          | ?                                    |\\n| 16          | ?                                    |\\n\\n### getJourneys(from, to, add\\\\_offers, date)\\n\\nreturns a promise, that resolves to routes from to at `date`. To add the offers, if they exist, set `add_offers` to `true`.`add_offers` is by default false.`date` is a node-datetime object. It has to be imported through npm\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n\\noebb.searchStationsNew(\\\"Wien Hbf\\\").then((res)=>{\\n\\tvar from = res[0];\\n\\toebb.searchStationsNew(\\\"Venezia Santa Lucia\\\").then((res)=>{\\n\\t\\tvar to=res[0];\\n\\t\\toebb.getJourneys(from, to, true).then((res)=>{\\n            console.log(res);\\n        });\\n\\t})\\n});\\n\\n####`from` and `to`they are formated:\\n\\nfrom/to = { \\n\\tnumber: 1190100,\\n    longitude: 16372134,\\n    latitude: 48208547,\\n    name: ''Wien'',\\n};\\n\\nThis returns for example (`connections` describes the journey navigation\\n\\n* README\\n* ISC license\\n\\n# oebb-hafas\\n\\n**Client for the Austrian Railways (BB) HAFAS API.** It acts as a consistent and straightforward interface on top of a verbose API.\\n\\nThis project is actually a thin wrapper around hafas-client. Its docs document the API in general.\\n\\nnpm version license chat on gitter\\n\\n## Installing\\n\\nnpm install oebb-hafas\\n\\n## API\\n\\nCheck the docs for hafas-client as well as the BB-specific customisations.\\n\\n## Getting Started\\n\\nconst hafas = require(''oebb-hafas'')(''your-user-agent'')\\n\\nAs an example, we will search for a route from _Wien Westbahnhof_ to _Salzburg Hbf_. To get the station ids, use locations(query, \\\\[opt\\\\]).\\n\\nclient.journeys(''1291501'', ''8100002'')\\n.then((journeys) => console.log(journeys[0]))\\n.catch(console.error)\\n\\n## Similar                       |                                                                                      |                     |                  |\\n\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n* README\\n* ISC license\\n\\n# oebb\\n\\nClient for the Austrian Federal Railways (BB) API. Inofficial, using endpoints by _BB_. Ask them for permission before using this module in production. **Actually, there should be no need for projects like this since endpoints for state-owned public transportation operators should be open to the public. It''s ~~2017, 2018, 2019,~~ 2020\\\\. By the way: Even Deutsche Bahn gets this now, and you don''t ever want to be less progressive than them, because that would hurt their pride .**\\n\\nThis module conforms to the FPTI-JS 0.3.2 standard for JavaScript public transportation modules.\\n\\nnpm version Build Status license fpti-js version\\n\\n## Installation\\n\\nnpm install oebb\\n\\n## Usage\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb'')\\n\\nThe `oebb` module conforms to the FPTI-JS 0.3.2 standard for JavaScript public transportation modules and exposes the following methods:\\n\\n| Method                                                                    | Feature description         | [FPTI-JS 0.3.2](https://github.com/public-transport/fpti-js/tree/0.3.2)                               |\\n| ------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| [stations.search(query, \\\\[opt\\\\])](#stationssearchquery-opt)               | Search stations by _query_. | [ yes](https://github.com/public-transport/fpti-js/blob/0.3.2/docs/stations-stops-regions.search.md) |\\n| [journeys(origin, destination, \\\\[opt\\\\])](#journeysorigin-destination-opt) | Journeys between stations   | [ yes](https://github.com/public-transport/fpti-js/blob/0.3.2/docs/journeys.md)                      |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `stations.search(query, [opt])`\\n\\nSearch stations by _query_. See this method in the FPTI-JS 0.3.2 spec.\\n\\n#### Supported Options\\n\\n| Attribute | Description                     | FPTI-spec | Value type | Default |\\n| --------- | ------------------------------- | --------- | ---------- | ------- |\\n| results   | Max. number of results returned |          | Number     | null    |\\n\\n#### Example\\n\\noebb.stations.search(''Wie'', { results: 2 }).then()\\n\\n[\\n\\t\\t{\\n\\t\\t\\ttype: ''station'',\\n\\t\\t\\tid: ''1190100'',\\n\\t\\t\\tname: ''Wien'',\\n\\t\\t\\tmeta: true, // indicates that this is a \\\"meta\\\" station, actually representing a group of stations, corresponding to the city of vienna in this case\\n\\t\\t\\tlocation: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''location'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlongitude: 16.372134,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlatitude: 48.208547\\n\\t\\t\\t}\\n\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t{\\n\\t\\t\\ttype: ''station'',\\n\\t\\t\\tid: ''1290401'',\\n\\t\\t\\tname: ''Wien Hbf (U)'',\\n\\t\\t\\tmeta: false,\\n\\t\\t\\tlocation: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''location'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlongitude: 16.375326,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlatitude: 48.185507\\n\\t\\t\\t}\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t]\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `journeys(origin, destination, [opt])`\\n\\nFind journeys between stations. See this method in the FPTI-JS 0.3.2 spec.\\n\\n#### Supported Options\\n\\n| Attribute      | Description                                                                   | FPTI-spec | Value type                                                                                      | Default    |\\n| -------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------- |\\n| when           | Journey date, synonym to departureAfter                                       |          | [Date](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global%5FObjects/date) | new Date() |\\n| departureAfter | List journeys with a departure (first leg) after this date                    |          | [Date](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global%5FObjects/date) | new Date() |\\n| results        | Max. number of results returned                                               |          | Number                                                                                          | null       |\\n| interval       | Results for how many minutes after when/departureAfter                        |          | Number                                                                                          | null       |\\n| transfers      | Max. number of transfers                                                      |          | Number                                                                                          | null       |\\n| prices         | Add price information to journeys (spawning an additional request internally) |          | Boolean                                                                                         | true       |\\n\\n#### Example\\n\\nconst berlin = ''8011160'' // station id\\nconst vienna = { // FPTF station\\n    type: ''station'',\\n    id: ''1190100'',\\n    name: ''Wien''\\n    // \\n}\\n\\noebb.journeys(berlin, vienna, { when: new Date(''2019-11-02T05:00:00+02:00''), results: 1 }).then()\\n\\n[\\n\\t{\\n\\t\\ttype: ''journey'',\\n\\t\\tid: ''fb829242f221c309fb7fecf4fe87a7e169c084b23274d3c1d1f1a1ce2aed040b'',\\n\\t\\tlegs: [\\n\\t\\t\\t{\\n\\t\\t\\t\\torigin: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''station'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tid: ''8098160'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''Berlin Hbf (tief)''\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tdestination: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''station'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tid: ''8010205'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''Leipzig Hbf''\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tdeparture: ''2019-11-02T04:28:00+01:00'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tdeparturePlatform: ''2'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tarrival: ''2019-11-02T05:42:00+01:00'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tarrivalPlatform: ''12'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\thasRealtimeInformation: false,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tline: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''line'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tid: ''ICE 501'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''ICE 501'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tnumber: ''501'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tproduct: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''ICE'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tshortName: ''ICE'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tlongName: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tde: ''Intercity Express'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ten: ''Intercity Express'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tit: ''Intercity express''\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t}\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tmode: ''train'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tpublic: true,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\toperator: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''https://www.oebb.at/''\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t}\\n\\t\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t\\t{\\n\\t\\t\\t\\torigin: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''station'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tid: ''8010205'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''Leipzig ''2019-11-02T09:26:00+01:00'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tarrivalPlatform: null,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\thasRealtimeInformation: false,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tline: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''line'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tid: ''EC 259'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''EC 259'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tnumber: ''259'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tproduct: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''EC'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tshortName: ''EC'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tlongName: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tde: ''Eurocity'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ten: ''Eurocity'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tit:                                      |                                                                                                                                                                                      |                     |                  |\\n\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n* README\\n* Apache-2.0 license\\n\\nAuthor: Peter Hirzel (Software Architect SBB Journey Planner), 2023  \\nLicence: Apache License, Version 2.0\\n\\n# About OJP-Adapter\\n\\nThe project contains 2 targets:\\n\\n1. a simple **OJPAdapter _library_** to request Public-Transportation queries against the **swiss public _Open Journey-Planner (SKI)_** based on OJP Specification OJP.xsd.\\n2. a RESTful **OJPController** with a Transmodel implemenation of a Journey-Planner interface\\n\\nRemark about **OJP SKI+**\\n\\n* Public Transportation router commissioned by BAV\\n* Usage for e.g. by v-info.ch\\n* OJP Wiki\\n* OJP-Demo shell and XML insights\\n\\n## Goals\\n\\nAbstracting the complex VDV OJP.xsd Schema by Java POJOs, map response properly and provide low-level error-handling.\\n\\nAnyone (for e.g. public transport-organisation) who plans to use the Swiss OJP router (or other european OJP instances supporting the same protocol version) may try this library to setup a quick working starting point.\\n\\nThe vdv ojp XSD might be quite complex and JAXB POJO generation therefore too!  \\nBesides, understanding the OJP semantics may mean a steep learning curve for non-insiders.\\n\\nThe author hopes using this OJP-Adapter library may \\\"abstract\\\" the above steps massively, though the resulting OJP model may still be complex to deal with (perhaps check the returned data for a more intuitive understanding as well).\\n\\n## Known usage\\n\\nThis Software was originally developed for _SBB AG Switzerland, Personenverkehr, CustomerInformation_ by Peter Hirzel (Software Architect Journey-Planner) for experimental reasons:\\n\\n* APIs (endpoints) under **SBB Journey-Service** within tag **Open Journey Planner V3**\\n\\n## Targets\\n\\n### OJPAdapter _library_\\n\\nContains:\\n\\n* the **OJP**.xsd **1.0** is transformed into a JAVA POJO (by JAXB) by  \\n   * open-source bliksemlabs or Maven  \\n   * dependency ojp-java-model\\n* Further documentation:  \\n   * Semantic model description OJP v1 - Open API for distributed Journey Planning by jmaerki\\n\\nThe provided **OJPAdapter** is able to query Swiss SKI+ OJP instances, if configured well (by means your own access token):\\n\\n* use _OJPAadapter_ for raw native XML handling in conversation with OJP protocol.\\n* Use of Swiss SKI+ OJP 2.0 API.\\n* Demonstration of easy filters and response analysis by **OJPAdapterAccessTest**\\n\\nSee:\\n\\n* VDV OJP 2.0 Model base for Java model Doc\\n* OJP 2.0 Cookbook\\n* OJP 2.0 Demo\\n* OJP 2.0 API Explorer (OpenApi 3)\\n\\n### OJPController _RESTful Service_\\n\\nContains:\\n\\n* OJP/Transmodel mapping\\n* SpringBoot **OJPWebApplication**\\n* * **OJPController** like subset of **SBB Journey-Service** v3 APIs where supported by SKI+ OJP:\\n* Transmodel like implementation model as used by SBB Customer Information\\n* Covers **Place, Trip, DatedVehicleJourney (including Departures/Arrivals)**\\n\\n## Run it\\n\\n### OJP-Adapter \\n\\n1. Download repository\\n2. mvn clean install\\n3. copy ojp-adapter-integration/src/main/resources/ojp-SAMPLE.properties to ojp.properties and add your own key for SKI+ OJP Instance from opentransportdata.swiss **passive instance** v2 _\\\"Manage the API key\\\"_\\n4. run swiss.opentransportdata.ojp.adapter.\\\\*\\\\*.OJPAdapterAccessTest (to try out native OJP XML based request/response)\\n\\n### OJPWebApplication \\n\\n1. clone ojp-adapter-service/main/resources/application.yml to application-local.yml and set ''ojp.authorization''\\n2. run swiss.opentransportdata.ojp.adapter.service.application.**OJPWebApplication** with ''VM Options''=-Dspring.profiles.active=local\\n3. open OpenAPI 3 Swagger-UI\\n\\nRemark:\\n\\n* At least the OJP passive key should be easy to get.\\n* For the OJP active instance key you probably need to contact the operation-responsibles.\\n* If your just interested in Open API 3 Swagger-UI resulting out of ojp-adapter-service/../**OJPController**, see JSON-specification\\n\\n## History\\n\\n### ~~OJP v1.0 implementation (DEPRECATED)~~\\n\\nSee OJP-Adapter v0.9.0-beta\\n\\n* Checkout if you need to acces SKI+ OJP active instance, which supports only OJP v1.\\\\*\\n* **Currently, OJPAdapter deals with one SINGLE Journey-Planner request at a time**, though MULTIPLE requests could be performed at once.\\n* Complete OJP set of request-filters (currently the most relevant filters are adapted).\\n* Complete OJP response mapping (currently the most relevant properties are implemented).\\n* Quality tests for correctly mapped output should be verified and confirmed by SKI+.\\n\\n## About\\n\\n Open Journey Planner library to simplify request/response handling\\n\\nopentransportdata.swiss/de/dataset/ojp2020 \\n\\n### Topics\\n\\n public-transportation  router  journey-planner \\n\\n### Resources\\n\\n Readme \\n\\n### License\\n\\n Apache-2.0 license \\n\\nActivity \\n\\nCustom properties \\n\\n### Stars\\n\\n**4** stars \\n\\n### Watchers\\n\\n**4** watching \\n\\n### Forks\\n\\n**0** forks \\n\\n Report repository \\n\\n## Authentication object\\n * @param {number|string} stationId - The station ID to get information for\\n * @param {Object} options - Options for the query\\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} - Station board data\\n */\\nfunction getStationBoard(auth, stationId, options = {}) {\\n    // Set default options\\n    const defaultOptions = {\\n        boardType: ''dep'', // ''dep'' for departures, ''arr'' for arrivals\\n        date: new Date().toISOString().split(''T'')[0], // Today in YYYY-MM-DD format\\n        time: new Date().toTimeString().slice(0, 5), // Current time in HH:MM format\\n    };\\n    \\n    const queryOptions = { ...defaultOptions, ...options };\\n    \\n    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\\n        console.log(`Fetching ${queryOptions.boardType === ''dep'' ? ''departures'' : ''arrivals''} for station ${stationId}`);\\n        console.log(`Date: ${queryOptions.date}, Time: ${queryOptions.time}`);\\n        \\n        request({\\n            url: \\\"https://tickets.oebb.at/api/hafas/v1/timetable/station/board\\\",\\n            json: true,\\n            qs: {\\n                direction: ''both'',\\n                localtime: true,\\n                stationId: stationId,\\n                type: queryOptions.boardType,\\n                date: queryOptions.date,\\n                time: queryOptions.time,\\n            },\\n            method: \\\"GET\\\",\\n            headers: {\\n                cookie: `ts-cookie=${auth.cookie}`,\\n                Channel: auth.channel,\\n                AccessToken: auth.accessToken,\\n                SessionId: auth.sessionId,\\n                ''x-ts-supportid'': \\\"WEB_\\\" + auth.supportId\\n            }\\n        }, (error, response, body) => {\\n            if (error) {\\n                reject(error);\\n                return;\\n            }\\n            \\n            if (!body) {\\n                reject(new Error(\\\"No body in station board response\\\"));\\n                return;\\n            }\\n            \\n            // Save the response to a file for debugging\\n            const fs = await import(''fs'');\\n            fs.writeFileSync(''station_board.json'', JSON.stringify(body, null, 2));\\n            console.log(''Response saved to station_board.json'');\\n            \\n            resolve(body);\\n        });\\n    });\\n}\\n\\n/**\\n * Check departures/arrivals at a station\\n * @param {number|string} stationId - The station ID\\n * @param {Object} options - Options for the query\\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} - Station board data\\n */\\nexport async function checkStationBoard(stationId, options = {}) {\\n    try {\\n        const auth = await authenticate();\\n        const boardData = await getStationBoard(auth, stationId, options);\\n        \\n        if (!boardData.boardEntries || !boardData.boardEntries.length) {\\n            console.log(\\\"No trains found at this station\\\");\\n            return { error: \\\"No trains found at this station\\\" };\\n        }\\n        \\n        console.log(`Found ${boardData.boardEntries.length} trains at ${boardData.station?.name || stationId}`);\\n        \\n        // Display train information with delay status\\n        boardData.boardEntries.forEach((train, index) => {\\n            const trainName = `${train.transport?.name || ''''} ${train.transport?.number || ''''}`.trim();\\n            const scheduledDep = train.departure?.scheduledTime || ''N/A'';\\n            const actualDep = train.departure?.actualTime || scheduledDep;\\n            const delayed = scheduledDep !== actualDep;\\n            const delayStatus = delayed ? `DELAYED (${actualDep})` : ''On time'';\\n            const cancelled = train.cancelled === true ? ''CANCELLED'' : '''';\\n            \\n            console.log(`${index + 1}. ${trainName} to ${train.transport?.destination?.name || ''Unknown''}`);\\n            console.log(`   Scheduled: ${scheduledDep}, Status: ${cancelled || delayStatus}`);\\n            console.log(`   Platform: ${train.platform?.actual || train.platform?.scheduled || ''N/A''}`);\\n        });\\n        \\n        return boardData;\\n    } catch (error) {\\n        console.error(''Error:'', error);\\n        throw error;\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n// Run demo if executed directly\\nif (process.argv[1].endsWith(''train-delay.js'')) {\\n    // Get station ID from command line or use Wien Hbf as default\\n    const stationId = process.argv[2] || ''1290401''; // Wien Hbf (U)\\n    \\n    console.log(`Checking train departures at station ID: ${stationId}`);\\n    \\n    // ES Module fix for importing fs dynamically\\n    const fixDynamicImport = `\\n    try {\\n      const dynamicImport = new Function(''specifier'', ''return import(specifier)'');\\n      globalThis.dynamicImport = dynamicImport;\\n    } catch (error) {\\n      console.warn(''Dynamic import not available:'', error);\\n    }\\n    `;\\n    eval(fixDynamicImport);\\n    \\n    checkStationBoard(stationId)\\n        .then(data => {\\n            console.log(''Done!'');\\n        })\\n        .catch(error => {\\n            console.error(''Failed:'', error);\\n            process.exit(1);\\n        });\\n}\\nEOF\", \"is_background\": \"false\"}","name":"run_terminal_cmd","additionalData":{"status":"error"},"error":"{\"clientVisibleErrorMessage\":\"Tool run_terminal_cmd not found. Try switching to Agent mode.\",\"modelVisibleErrorMessage\":\"Tool run_terminal_cmd not found. Available tools: [\\\"codebase_search\\\",\\\"read_file\\\",\\\"list_dir\\\",\\\"grep_search\\\",\\\"file_search\\\",\\\"web_search\\\"]\"}"}}');

<http://gueterfahrplan.hacon.de/bin/db/ajax-getstop.exe> or http://gterfahrplan.hacon.de/bin/db/ajax-getstop.exe\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) doesn''t work.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) shows the regular version.\\n\\nExtra feature: <http://db-erreichbarkeit.hafas.de/bin/query.exe>\\n\\n#### historical version\\n\\n* <http://db-mobilitaetsvergleich.hafas.de/bin/query.exe>\\n\\n#### protected version\\n\\n* <http://db-zugradar.hafas.de/bin/schenker/extxml.exe>\\n* <http://db-zugradar.hafas.de/bin/schenker/query.exe>\\n* <http://db-zugradar.hafas.de/bin/schenker/stboard.exe>\\n* <http://db-zugradar.hafas.de/bin/schenker/ajax-getstop.exe>\\n* <http://db-zugradar.hafas.de/bin/schenker/help.exe> (map with all trains)\\n\\nThis version ist HTTP basic auth protected (unencrypted).\\n\\n### BVG (Berlin)\\n\\n* <http://fahrinfo.bvg.de/Fahrinfo/bin/extxml.bin> or <http://mobil.bvg.de/Fahrinfo/bin/extxml.bin>\\n* <http://fahrinfo.bvg.de/Fahrinfo/bin/query.bin> or <http://mobil.bvg.de/Fahrinfo/bin/query.bin>\\n* <http://fahrinfo.bvg.de/Fahrinfo/bin/stboard.bin> or <http://mobil.bvg.de/Fahrinfo/bin/stboard.bin>\\n* <http://fahrinfo.bvg.de/Fahrinfo/bin/ajax-getstop.bin> or <http://mobil.bvg.de/Fahrinfo/bin/ajax-getstop.bin>\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works (only on `fahrinfo.bvg.de`, but not on `mobil.bvg.de`).\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) works.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) shows to the regular version.\\n\\n#### weird version\\n\\nThis installation serves the old BVG landing page, even though it has the latest data.\\n\\n* <http://bvg.hafas.de/bin/query.exe>\\n* <http://bvg.hafas.de/bin/help.exe/dn?L=vs%5Flivefahrplan&tpl=livefahrplan> (map with all busses)\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) shows the text version (`/el`).\\n\\nText version (`/el`) shows to the regular version.\\n\\n### S-Bahn Mnchen (Munich)\\n\\n* <http://s-bahn-muenchen.hafas.de/bin/query.exe> (empty response)\\n* <http://s-bahn-muenchen.hafas.de/bin/stboard.exe> (weird old ui!)\\n* <http://s-bahn-muenchen.hafas.de/bin/ajax-getstop.exe>\\n* <http://s-bahn-muenchen.hafas.de/bin/help.exe/dn?tpl=livefahrplan> (modern, map with all trains)\\n\\nRegular version (`/dn`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/dox`) is just hilarious.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) works.\\n\\n### VBB (Berlin & Brandenburg)\\n\\nvbb-hafas\\n\\nSee <https://gist.github.com/anonymous/9203ea600333470be8f5af4e0761b03c> for more details.\\n\\n* <http://fahrinfo.vbb.de/bin/extxml.exe>\\n* <http://fahrinfo.vbb.de/bin/query.exe>\\n* <http://fahrinfo.vbb.de/bin/stboard.exe>\\n* <http://fahrinfo.vbb.de/bin/ajax-getstop.exe>\\n* <http://fahrinfo.vbb.de/bin/help.exe/dn?L=vs%5Fmobilitymap&tpl=fullmap&tabApp=show> (map with all trains)\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) shows the (responsive) regular version.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) doesn''t work.\\n\\nSupports EU-Spirit (`switchEuspirit=yes`).\\n\\nSupports DELFI (`iER=yes`).\\n\\n#### another version\\n\\n* Help me complete this list!\\n\\n_todo: <http://www.fahrplanauskunftssysteme.de/?seitenID=27>_\\n\\n## Deutsche Bahn (Germany)\\n\\n* <http://mobile.bahn.de/bin/extxml.exe> or <http://reiseauskunft.bahn.de/bin/ajax-getstop.exe> or <http://mobile.bahn.de/bin/ajax-getstop.exe>\\n* <http://www.apps-bahn.de/bin/livemap/query-livemap.exe/dn?L=vs%5Flivefahrplan&livemap=yes> (map with all trains)\\n\\n## DB Schenker (Germany)\\n\\nDB Schenker ist the logistics branch of Deutsch Bahn.\\n\\n* <http://gueterfahrplan.hacon.de/bin/db/query.exe> or http://gterfahrplan.hacon.de/bin/db/query.exe\\n* <http://gueterfahrplan.hacon.de/bin/db/stboard.exe> or http://gterfahrplan.hacon.de/bin/db/stboard.exe\\n* <http://gueterfahrplan.hacon.de/bin/db/ajax-getstop.exe> or http://gterfahrplan.hacon.de/bin/db/ajax-getstop.exe\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) doesn''t work.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) shows the regular version.\\n\\nExtra feature: <http://db-erreichbarkeit.hafas.de/bin/query.exe>\\n\\n### historical version\\n\\n* Abhngig von Ort und ausgewhltem HAFAS-Service kann es Fahrten des Regional-/Fernverkehrs oder auch das lokale Nahverkehrsangebot mit Echtzeitdaten anzeigen. Hinweise zur Installation und eine Liste untersttzter Backends finden sich im Travel::Status::DE::HAFAS README.\\n\\n**hafas-m** is a comamndline client for HAFAS-based arrival/departure monitors. It shows arrivals or departures of trains as well as local transit services. The level of detail depends on the selected HAFAS service. See theTravel::Status::DE::HAFAS READMEfor installation instructions and supported services.\\n\\n## Abfahrtstafel (departure board)\\n\\n```\\n> hafas-m ''Dortmund Universitt''\\n15:11      Schw-B HB2  Campus Sd, Dortmund\\n15:13  +1  S 1         Dortmund Hbf                    2\\n15:15      Schw-B HB1  Technologiezentrum, Dortmund\\n15:15      Schw-B HB1  Eichlinghofen H-Bahn, Dortmund\\n15:16      Schw-B HB2  Campus Sd, Dortmund\\n15:18  +1  S 1         Essen Hbf                       1\\n15:18      Bus 447     Bandelstrae, Dortmund\\n15:20      Bus 447     Hacheney, Dortmund\\n\\n```\\n\\n## Stationssuche (station search)\\n\\n```\\n> hafas-m ''?Universitt''\\n 8006513  Stuttgart Universitt\\n 8000453  Freiburg Messe/Universitt\\n 8004419  Dortmund Universitt\\n 8070769  Bonn Universitt/Markt\\n\\n\\n> hafas-m ''51.21277:6.79956''\\n  0.2 km    366253  Flgelstrae, Dsseldorf\\n  0.2 km    369007  Kruppstrae, Dsseldorf\\n  0.2 km    653532  Gangelplatz, Dsseldorf\\n\\n```\\n\\n## Zuginfo (train details)\\n\\n```\\n> hafas-m ''!ICE 947''\\nICE 947  Berlin Ostbahnhof / Zug 947 / Linie 10\\nFahrt 1|177182|0|81|1012024 am 01.01.2024\\n\\n        19:52           Dsseldorf Hbf  Berlin Ostbahnhof\\n19:58  20:00       ..  Dsseldorf Flughafen\\n20:08  20:10       ..  Duisburg Hbf\\n20:21  20:23       ..  Essen Hbf\\n20:33  20:34       ..  Bochum Hbf\\n20:45  20:48       ..  Dortmund Hbf\\n21:13  21:17 (+6)  .o  Hamm(Westf)Hbf\\n21:42  21:44 (+6)  .o  Bielefeld Hbf\\n22:32  22:34 (+3)  .o  Hannover Hbf\\n23:05  23:06 (+2)  .o  Wolfsburg Hbf\\n23:34  23:36 (+4)  .o  Stendal Hbf\\n00:11                   Berlin-Spandau\\n00:27                   Berlin Hbf\\n00:37                   Berlin Ostbahnhof\\n\\n```\\n\\n2025-03-25 \\n\\n# Travel::Status::DE::HAFAS v6.20\\n\\nTravel-Status-DE-HAFAS-6.20.tar.gz (signature)\\n\\n* hafas-m: Change default service to BB\\n* hafas-m: Add `--with-polyline` option\\n* Disable certificate verification for KVB HAFAS service when using the `new_p` constructor (see 6.19)\\n\\n2025-03-06 \\n\\n# Travel::Status::DE::HAFAS v6.19\\n\\nTravel-Status-DE-HAFAS-6.19.tar.gz (signature)\\n\\n* Remove VRN HAFAS service (discontinued, returns HTTP 403 Forbidden)\\n* Disable certiicate verification for KVB HAFAS service (they bodged their certificate renewal)\\n\\n2025-02-09 \\n\\n# Travel::Status::DE::HAFAS v6.18\\n\\nTravel-Status-DE-HAFAS-6.18.tar.gz (signature)\\n\\n* Add PKP service. Note that it is GeoIP-locked to \\\"probably Polish\\\" IP addresses. Set `HAFAS_PROXY_PKP` to a suitable proxy address to work around this, if needed.\\n\\n2025-01-19 \\n\\n# Travel::Status::DE::HAFAS v6.17\\n\\nTravel-Status-DE-HAFAS-6.17.tar.gz (signature)\\n\\n* Various documentation updates to reflect on the DB HAFAS removal\\n\\n2025-01-13 \\n\\n# Travel::Status::DE::HAFAS v6.16\\n\\nTravel-Status-DE-HAFAS-6.16.tar.gz (signature)\\n\\n* Remove DB HAFAS service. Usage\\n\\n### Connections between stations\\n\\n1. Authentication\\n2. Find Stations for start and destination\\n3. information (departures or arrivals)\n * @param {Object} auth - Authentication object\n * @param {number|string} stationId - The station ID to get information for\n * @param {Object} options - Options for the query\n * @param {string} options.boardType - Type of board (''dep'' for departures, ''arr'' for arrivals)\n * @param {string} options.date - Optional date in YYYY-MM-DD format\n * @param {string} options.time - Optional time in HH:MM format\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} - Station board data\n */\nfunction getStationBoardData(auth, stationId, options = {}) {\n    // Set default options\n    const defaultOptions = {\n        boardType: ''dep'', // ''dep'' for departures, ''arr'' for arrivals\n        // API uses current server time if date/time not provided\n    };\n\n    const queryOptions = { ...defaultOptions, ...options };\n    const apiUrl = \"https://tickets.oebb.at/api/hafas/v1/timetable/station/board\";\n\n    const qsParams = {\n        direction: ''both'', // Can be ''departure'', ''arrival'', or ''both''\n        localtime: true,\n        stationId: stationId,\n        type: queryOptions.boardType,\n    };\n\n    if (queryOptions.date) {\n        qsParams.date = queryOptions.date;\n    }\n    if (queryOptions.time) {\n        qsParams.time = queryOptions.time;\n    }\n\n    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n        request({\n            url: apiUrl,\n            json: true,\n            qs: qsParams,\n            method: \"GET\",\n            headers: {\n                cookie: `ts-cookie=${auth.cookie}`, // Still sending, though might not be strictly needed\n                Channel: auth.channel,\n                AccessToken: auth.accessToken,\n                SessionId: auth.sessionId,\n                ''x-ts-supportid'': \"WEB_\" + auth.supportId\n            }\n        }, (error, response, body) => {\n            if (error) {\n                reject(error);\n                return;\n            }\n            if (!body) {\n                reject(new Error(\"No body in station board response\"));\n                return;\n            }\n            if (response.statusCode !== 200) {\n                reject(new Error(`API Error: ${response.statusCode} - ${JSON.stringify(body)}`));\n                return;\n            }\n            resolve(body);\n        });\n    });\n}\n\n/**\n * Public function to get station board data\n * @param {number|string} stationId - The station ID\n * @param {Object} options - Options for the query (boardType, date, time)\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} Station board data\n */\nexport function getStationBoard(stationId, options = {}) {\n    return authenticate().then(auth => {\n        return getStationBoardData(auth, stationId, options);\n    });\n}\n\n\n/**\n * Check options - Options for the query (boardType, date, time)\n * @returns {Promise<Object>} - Delay information or error\n */\nexport function checkTrainDelay(stationId, trainNumber, options = {}) {\n    return getStationBoard(stationId, options)\n        .then(boardData => {\n            if (!boardData.boardEntries || !boardData.boardEntries.length) {\n                return { error: \"No trains found at this station for the given time.\" };\n            }\n\n            const trainInfo = boardData.boardEntries.find(entry => {\n                const entryName = entry.transport?.name || trainNumber.toLowerCase() ||\n                       entryName.toLowerCase() === trainNumber.toLowerCase() ||\n                       entryNum.toLowerCase() === trainNumber.toLowerCase();\n            });\n\n            if (!trainInfo) {\n                return {\n                    error: `Train \"${trainNumber}\" not found at station ${boardData.station?.name || stationId}.`,\n                    // To help debugging, list available trains\n                    availableTrains: boardData.boardEntries.map(entry => ({\n                        name: `${entry.transport?.name || ''''} ${entry.transport?.number || ''''}`.trim(),\n                        destination: entry.transport?.destination?.name || ''N/A'',\n                        scheduled: options.boardType === ''arr'' ? entry.arrival?.scheduledTime : entry.departure?.scheduledTime\n                    })).slice(0,10) // Show first 10\n                };\n            }\n\n            const boardType = options.boardType || ''dep'';\n            const timeInfo = boardType === ''arr'' ? trainInfo.arrival : trainInfo.departure;\n\n            const scheduledTimeStr = timeInfo?.scheduledTime;\n            const actualTimeStr = timeInfo?.actualTime || scheduledTimeStr; // If no actualTime, assume on time\n\n            let delayMinutes = 0;\n            let isDelayed = false;\n\n            if (scheduledTimeStr && actualTimeStr) {\n                const queryDate = options.date || new Date().toISOString().split(''T'')[0];\n                const scheduledDateTime = new Date(`${queryDate}T${scheduledTimeStr}`);\n                const actualDateTime = new Date(`${queryDate}T${actualTimeStr}`);\n                \n                if (!isNaN(scheduledDateTime) && !isNaN(actualDateTime)) {\n                    const delayMs = actualDateTime - scheduledDateTime;\n                    delayMinutes = Math.round(delayMs / 60000);\n                    isDelayed = delayMinutes > 0;\n                }\n            }\n            \n            return {\n                train: `${trainInfo.transport?.name || ''''} ${trainInfo.transport?.number || ''''}`.trim(),\n                station: boardData.station?.name || stationId,\n                type: boardType === ''arr'' ? ''Arrival'' : ''Departure'',\n                scheduledTime: scheduledTimeStr || ''N/A'',\n                actualTime: actualTimeStr || ''N/A'',\n                platform: {\n                    scheduled: timeInfo?.platform?.scheduled || ''N/A'',\n                    actual: timeInfo?.platform?.actual || timeInfo?.platform?.scheduled || ''N/A'',\n                    changed: timeInfo?.platform?.changed || false,\n                },\n                destination: trainInfo.transport?.destination?.name || ''N/A'',\n                origin: trainInfo.transport?.origin?.name || ''N/A'',\n                cancelled: trainInfo.cancelled === true,\n                delayMinutes: delayMinutes,\n                isDelayed: isDelayed,\n                messages: trainInfo.messages || []\n            };\n        });\n}\n\n// ... existing code ...\n```\n\nNow, let''s update `demo.js` to use this new function.\n\n```javascript:demo.js\n#!/usr/bin/env node\n\nimport { searchStations, searchAndDisplayStations, checkTrainDelay, getStationBoard } from ''./oebb-direct.js'';\n\nasync function main() {\n    const command = process.argv[2];\n    const arg1 = process.argv[3];\n    const arg2 = process.argv[4];\n    const arg3 = process.argv[5]; // For date/time options\n\n    if (command === ''search'') {\n        const stationName = arg1 || ''Wien'';\n        console.log(`Searching for stations matching \"${stationName}\"...`);\n        try {\n            const stations = await searchAndDisplayStations(stationName);\n            console.log(''\\nFull station details:'');\n            console.log(JSON.stringify(stations, null, 2));\n        } catch (error) {\n            console.error(''Failed to search for stations:'', error);\n            process.exit(1);\n        }\n    } else if (command === ''board'') {\n        const stationId = arg1 || ''1290401''; // Wien Hbf (U)\n        const boardType = arg2 || ''dep''; // ''dep'' or ''arr''\n        console.log(`Fetching ${boardType === ''dep'' ? ''departures'' : ''arrivals''} for station ID ${stationId}...`);\n        try {\n            const boardData = await getStationBoard(stationId, { boardType });\n            console.log(JSON.stringify(boardData, null, 2));\n        } catch (error) {\n            console.error(`Failed to get station board for ${stationId}:`, error);\n            process.exit(1);\n        }\n    } else if (command === ''delay'') {\n        const stationId = arg1; // e.g. 1290401 for Wien Hbf\n        const trainNumber = arg2; // e.g. \"RJ 74\"\n        \n        if (!stationId || !trainNumber) {\n            console.error(''Usage: node demo.js delay <stationId> <trainNumber> [YYYY-MM-DD] [HH:MM]'');\n            process.exit(1);\n        }\n\n        const date = process.argv[5];\n        const time = process.argv[6];\n        const options = { boardType: ''dep'' }; // Default to departures\n        if (date) options.date = date;\n        if (time) options.time = time;\n\n        console.log(`Checking delay for train \"${trainNumber}\" at station ID ${stationId}...`);\n        try {\n            const delayInfo = await checkTrainDelay(stationId, trainNumber, options);\n            console.log(JSON.stringify(delayInfo, null, 2));\n        } catch (error) {\n            console.error(`Failed to check delay for train \"${trainNumber}\":`, error);\n            process.exit(1);\n        }\n    } else {\n        console.log(''Usage:'');\n        console.log(''  node demo.js search [station_name]'');\n        console.log(''  node demo.js board <stationId> [dep|arr]'');\n        console.log(''  node demo.js delay <stationId> <trainNumber> [YYYY-MM-DD] [HH:MM]'');\n        console.log(''\\nExample: node demo.js delay 1290401 \"RJ 74\"'');\n    }\n}\n\nmain();\n```\nI''ve added a `getStationBoard` function and a `checkTrainDelay` function to `oebb-direct.js`. The `demo.js` script has been updated to include new commands:\n*   `board <stationId> [dep|arr]` to fetch the station board.\n*   `delay <stationId> <trainNumber> [YYYY-MM-DD] [HH:MM]` to check for a specific train''s delay.\n\nYou can try it out. For example, to check for \"RJ 74\" at Wien Hbf (U) (station ID 1290401):\n`node demo.js delay 1290401 \"RJ 74\"`\n\nKeep in mind that train schedules and real-time data change, so you''ll need to use a train number that is currently active or scheduled around the time you''re querying to get meaningful results. The API typically provides data for the current day and a limited future window.","isChat":false,"timingInfo":{"clientStartTime":636132.099999994,"clientRpcSendTime":1746645243746,"clientSettleTime":1746645274473,"clientEndTime":1746645274473},"intermediateChunks":[],"serverBubbleId":"3bc69d54-7159-4d57-ac53-8fe6d7fde3b2","usageUuid":"ea47f410-a8c4-4174-8790-96d0a247e86b","symbolLinks":["{\"symbolName\":\"oebb-direct.js\",\"symbolSearchString\":\"oebb\",\"relativeWorkspacePath\":\"test1.js\",\"roughLineNumber\":1}","{\"symbolName\":\"ts-cookie=${auth.cookie}\",\"symbolSearchString\":\"ts-cookie=${auth.cookie}\",\"relativeWorkspacePath\":\"test1.js\",\"roughLineNumber\":91}","{\"symbolName\":\"API Error: ${response.statusCode} - ${JSON.stringify(body)}\",\"symbolSearchString\":\"API\",\"relativeWorkspacePath\":\"README.md\",\"roughLineNumber\":7}","{\"symbolName\":\"getStationBoard\",\"symbolSearchString\":\"getStationBoard\",\"relativeWorkspacePath\":\"README.md\",\"roughLineNumber\":21}","{\"symbolName\":\"board <stationId> [dep|arr]\",\"symbolSearchString\":\"board\",\"relativeWorkspacePath\":\"node_modules/oebb-api/oebb.js\",\"roughLineNumber\":320}","{\"symbolName\":\"delay <stationId> <trainNumber> [YYYY-MM-DD] [HH:MM]\",\"symbolSearchString\":\"delay\",\"relativeWorkspacePath\":\"README.md\",\"roughLineNumber\":198}","{\"symbolName\":\"node demo.js delay 1290401 \\\"RJ 74\\\"\",\"symbolSearchString\":\"node\",\"relativeWorkspacePath\":\"package.json\",\"roughLineNumber\":8}"]}');

OEBB API Direct Client\n\nThis is a modern JavaScript client for the Austrian Federal Railways (BB) API, created to replace the outdated oebb-api npm package.\n\n## Background\n\nThe original This project provides a modern ES module alternative that works with the current API.\\n  \\n-  - [HAFAS Fahrplanauskunft API - Sammlung](https://www.administrator.de/wissen/hafas-fahrplanauskunft-api-sammlung-177145.html)\\n-  - [Austrian Federal Railways (BB) API client by juliuste](https://github.com/juliuste/oebb)\\n-  \\n- and a [documentation file](https://avb.rmv.de/vergabeverfahren/b-2020-lfd/1-qsv-avb/QSV_Anhang%203e%20%28Anlage%2017_Anh%206%20Realtime%20Datform%20HAFAS%20Parameter_MVU%20170803%29_AVB.pdf/view) I found on the web\\n+ ## Features\\n+ \\n+ - Search for train stations by name\\n+ - Modern ES module syntax\\n+ - Promise-based API\\n+ - Works with current BB API (as of May 2025)\\n  \\n  ## Installation\\n- ```shell\\n- npm --save install oebb-api\\n- ```\\n- ## Functions\\n- \\n-  - [searchStationsNew](#searchstationsnewname)\\n-  - [searchStations](#searchstationsoptions)\\n-  - [getJourneys](#getjourneysfrom-to-addoffers-date)\\n-  - [getStationBoardData](#getstationboarddataoptions)\\n-  - [getStationBoardDataOptions](#getstationboarddataoptions-1)\\n-  - [getStationSearchOptions](#getstationsearchoptions)\\n- \\n- ### searchStationsNew(name)\\n- It returns an promise that resolves to an array of possible stations matching `name`\\n- ```javascript\\n- const oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n- \\n- oebb.searchStationsNew(\\\"Wien\\\").then(console.log);\\n- ```\\n- returns\\n+ \\n+ ```bash\\n+ npm install request\\n+ ```\\n+ \\n+ ## Usage\\n+ \\n+ ### Basic Search\\n+ \\n  ```javascript\\n- [{ number: 1190100,\\n-     longitude: 16372134,\\n-     latitude: 48208547,\\n-     name: '''',\\n-     meta: ''Wien'' },\\n-   { number: 1290401,\\n-     longitude: 16375326,\\n-     latitude: 48185507,\\n-     name: ''Wien Hbf (U)'',\\n-     meta: '''' },\\n- ...\\n- ...\\n- ...]\\n- ```\\n- ### searchStations(options)\\n- *searchStation* is very similar to [*searchStationsNew*](#searchstationsnewname) it however can take more [`options`](#options) and returns more information. You can call [getStationSearchOptions](#getstationsearchoptions) to get a prefilled options object.\\n- ```javascript\\n- const oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n- \\n- var options = oebb.getStationSearchOptions();\\n- options.S=\\\"wien h\\\";\\n- oebb.searchStations(options).then(console.log);\\n- ```\\n- It returns an array with matching stations, POIs, etc.\\n- ```javascript\\n- [ { value: ''Wien Hbf (U)'',\\n-     id: ''A=1@O=Wien Hbf (U)@X=16375326@Y=48185507@U=181@L=001290401@B=1@p=1513853468@'',\\n-     extId: ''001290401'',\\n-     type: ''1'',\\n-     typeStr: ''[Bhf/Hst]'',\\n-     xcoord: ''16375326'',\\n-     ycoord: ''48185507'',\\n-     state: ''id'',\\n-     prodClass: ''6013'',\\n-     weight: ''32767'' },\\n-   { value: ''Wien Meidling'',\\n-     id: ''A=1@O=Wien Meidling@X=16333211@Y=48174559@U=181@L=001191201@B=1@p=1513853468@'',\\n-     extId: ''001191201'',\\n-     type: ''1'',\\n-     typeStr: ''[Bhf/Hst]'',\\n-     xcoord: ''16333211'',\\n-     ycoord: ''48174559'',\\n-     state: ''id'',\\n-     prodClass: ''4989'',\\n-     weight: ''32588'' },\\n- ...\\n- ...\\n- ...]\\n- ```\\n- Name | description\\n- --- | ---\\n- value: | name of the station \\n- id  | no idea\\n- extId | used in other queries; same as number (not quite shure if the really are the same all the time) \\n- type | int representing the type\\n- typeStr | the type as string\\n- xcoord | longitude\\n- ycoord |latitude\\n- state | no idea\\n- prodClass| no idea\\n- weight | I am guessing it represents how close a match the station is to the string\\n- \\n- \\n- ### getStationSearchOptions()\\n- \\n- It returns an object containing the options for [searchStations](#searchstationsoptions)\\n+ import { searchStations } from ''./oebb-direct.js'';\\n+ \\n+ searchStations(''Wien'')\\n+   .then(stations => {\\n+     console.log(''Found stations:'', stations);\\n+   })\\n+   .catch(error => {\\n+     console.error(''Error:'', error);\\n+   });\\n+ ```\\n+ \\n+ ### Display Search Results\\n+ \\n  ```javascript\\n- const oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n- \\n- var options = oebb.getStationSearchOptions();\\n- ```\\n- \\n- #### options\\n- \\n- Name | default value | value | description\\n- --- | --- | --- |  --- |\\n- REQ0JourneyStopsS0A | 1 |  An int between 1 and 255. | It selects the type of station to return e.g. 1 is [Bhf/Hst]\\n- REQ0JourneyStopsB | 12 | An int greater 0 | the amount of results which are returned\\n- S | | a string | the string to match\\n- js |`true` | boolean | no idea what it does\\n- \\n- ### getStationBoardData(options)\\n- It returns a promise resolving to an object containing arrival or depature information for a specific station. You can get a prefilled [`options`](#options-1) object, by calling [getStationBoardDataOptions](#getstationboarddataoptions-1)\\n- ```javascript\\n- const oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n- \\n- var options = oebb.getStationBoardDataOptions();\\n- options.evaId=1191601;//Ottakring (Wien)\\n- oebb.getStationBoardData(options).then(console.log);\\n+ import { searchAndDisplayStations } from ''./oebb-direct.js'';\\n+ \\n+ searchAndDisplayStations(''Wien'')\\n+   .then(stations => {\\n+     // Do something with the stations\\n+     console.log(`Found ${stations.length} stations`);\\n+   });\\n  ```\\n- returns:\\n- ```javascript\\n- { headTexts:\\n-    [ ''Zeit'',\\n-      ''Fahrt'',\\n-      ''Nach'',\\n-      ''Steig'',\\n-      ''Abfahrten'',\\n-      ''Aktuell'',\\n-      ''Ankunft'' ],\\n-   stationName: ''Ottakring (Wien)'',\\n-   stationEvaId: ''1191601'',\\n-   boardType: ''dep'',\\n-   imgPath: ''/img/'',\\n-   iconProductsSubPath: ''vs_oebb/'',\\n-   rtInfo: true,\\n-   journey:\\n-    [ { id: ''875171810'',\\n-        ti: ''19:46'',\\n-        da: ''23.12.2017'',\\n-        pr: ''U3'',\\n-        st: ''Wien Simmering'',\\n-        lastStop: ''Wien Simmering Bahnhof (U3)'',\\n-        ati: ''20:12'',\\n-        tr: ''1'',\\n-        trChg: false,\\n-        rt: false,\\n-        rta: false },\\n-      { id: ''836641815'',\\n-        ti: ''19:46'',\\n-        da: ''23.12.2017'',\\n-        pr: ''Tram 46'',\\n-        st: ''Wien Ring/Volkstheater U'',\\n-        lastStop: ''Wien Dr.-K.-Renner-Ring/Volkstheater (Schleife)'',\\n-        ati: ''20:00'',\\n-        tr: '''',\\n-        trChg: ,\\n-        rt: { status: null, dlm: ''2'', dlt: ''19:47'' , dld:''23.12.2017''},\\n-        rta: false },\\n-        ...\\n-        ...\\n-        ...\\n-  ],\\n-   maxJ: 18 }\\n- \\n- ```\\n- #### element description\\n- ##### general:\\n- Name | description\\n- --- | --- \\n- headTexts | headings for arrivals depatures screen\\n- stationName | name of station\\n- stationEvaId | Id of station\\n- boardType | depatures or arrivals (dep/arr)\\n- imgPath | ?\\n- iconProductsSubPath | ?\\n- rtInfo | ?\\n- maxJ | number of returned entries -1\\n- \\n- ##### journey:\\n- \\n- Name | description\\n- --- | --- \\n- id | ?\\n- ti | arrvial/depature time\\n- da | arrival/depature date\\n- pr | name of transport\\n- st | ?\\n- lastStop | last stop\\n- ati | wehn arrivals depature time from first stop ; when depatures expected time to reach last stop\\n- tr | track identifier\\n- trChg | did the track change\\n- \\n- ##### rt :\\n- it describes the delay or other status if there is one. If there is one it contains an object formated as follows:\\n- \\n-  Name | description\\n-  --- | --- \\n-  status | current status; \\\"Ausfall\\\" if canceled\\n-  dlm | how many minutes too late\\n-  dlt | actual arrival time\\n-  dld | actual arrival date\\n- \\n- ##### rta \\n- it is very similar to rt I think it describes the delay for the arrival, but I am not certain.\\n- \\n- Name | description\\n- --- | --- \\n- status | current status  \\\"Ausfall\\\" if canceled then rt too is canceld and rt.status= \\\"Ausfall\\\"\\n- dlm | never seen it other than empty\\n- dlt | never seen it other than empty\\n- \\n- ### getStationBoardDataOptions()\\n- returns prefilled options for [getStationBoardData](#getstationboarddataoptions)\\n- ```javascript\\n- const oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n- \\n- var options = oebb.getStationBoardDataOptions();\\n- ```\\n- #### options\\n- \\n- Name | default value | values | description\\n- --- | --- | --- | ---\\n- L | vs_scotty.vs_liveticker|  vs_scotty.vs_liveticker | ?\\n- evaId | empty| integer | Id of station; extId or number from [searchStationsNew](#searchstationsnewname) or [searchStations](#searchstationsoptions)\\n- dirInput | empty| integer | Id of Station in which transportation is heading; extId or number f from [searchStationsNew](#searchstationsnewname) or [searchStations](#searchstationsoptions). If it is set only trains which actually stop at the station specified with dirInput are shown\\n- boardType | dep | dep/arr | depatures or arrivals\\n- time | current time| HH:MM | time from when to start looking\\n- productsFilter | 1111111111111111 | binary flags? | selects modes of transportation see [below](#productsfilter) for more information\\n- additionalTime | 0 | integer | in minute. Is added to time\\n- maxJourneys | 19 | integer | max of returned stations\\n- outputMode | tickerDataOnly | tickerDataOnly | ?\\n- start |yes| yes/no | wheter to start query\\n- selectDate | period | period/tody | selects mode; if tody dateBegin and dateEnd are ignored. \\n- dateBegin| current date | String dd.mm.YYYY | start day for lookup ignored if selectDate=today\\n- dateEnd | current date| String dd.mm.YYYY | end date for lookup ignored if selectDate=today\\n- \\n- ##### productsFilter\\n- slects which modes of transports should be listed\\n- forexample if I set `productsFilter` to 0000110000000000 only s-bahn and regionalzge are shown\\n- \\n- Flag number | mode of transport\\n-  --- |  ---\\n-  1 | railjet\\n-  2 | ?\\n-  3 | ec and ice\\n-  4 | nightjet d probably also nightjet en\\n-  5 | regionalzge\\n-  6 | s-bahn\\n-  7 | Bus\\n-  8 | ?\\n-  9 | subway\\n-  10 | tram\\n-  11 | ?\\n-  12 | ?\\n-  13 | Westbahn\\n-  14 | ?\\n-  15 | ?\\n-  16 | ?\\n-  \\n- ### getJourneys(from, to, add_offers, date)\\n- returns a promise, that resolves to routes [`from`](#from-and-to) [`to`](#from-and-to) at `date`. To add the offers, if they exist, set `add_offers` to `true`. \\n- `add_offers` is by default false. \\n- `date` is a node-datetime object. It has to be imported through npm\\n+ \\n+ ### Command Line Demo\\n+ \\n+ Run the demo script:\\n+ \\n+ ```bash\\n+ node demo.js [station_name]\\n+ ```\\n+ \\n+ Example:\\n+ ```bash\\n+ node demo.js Wien\\n+ node demo.js Linz\\n+ ```\\n+ \\n+ ## API Details\\n+ \\n+ ### Functions\\n+ \\n+ #### `searchStations(name, count = 15)`\\n+ \\n+ Searches for stations matching the given name.\\n+ \\n+ - **Parameters**:\\n+   - `name` (string): The station name to search for\\n+   - `count` (number, optional): Maximum number of results (default: 15)\\n+ - **Returns**: Promise that resolves to an array of station objects\\n+ \\n+ #### `searchAndDisplayStations(stationName)`\\n+ \\n+ Searches for stations and logs them to the console.\\n+ \\n+ - **Parameters**:\\n+   - `stationName` (string): The station name to search for\\n+ - **Returns**: Promise that resolves to an array of station objects\\n+ \\n+ ## Station Object Format\\n  \\n  ```javascript\\n- const oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n- \\t\\toebb.getJourneys(from, to, true).then((res)=>{\\n-             console.log(res);\\n-         });\\n- \\t})\\n- });\\n- ```\\n- ####`from` and `to` \\n- they are formated:\\n- ```javascript\\n- \"https://tickets.oebb.at/api/domain/v3/init\",\n            method: \"GET\",\n            json: true,\n            headers: { Channel: \"inet\" },\n            qs: { userId: userId },\n EU-Spirit (`/hafas/eu/query.exe`).\\n\\n## Luxembourg\\n\\n### Mobiliteitszentral (Luxembourg)\\n\\n* <http://mobiliteitszentral.hafas.de/hafas/extxml.exe> or <http://travelplanner.mobiliteit.lu/hafas/extxml.exe>\\n* <http://mobiliteitszentral.hafas.de/hafas/query.exe> or <http://travelplanner.mobiliteit.lu/hafas/query.exe>\\n* <http://mobiliteitszentral.hafas.de/hafas/stboard.exe> or <http://travelplanner.mobiliteit.lu/hafas/stboard.exe>\\n* <http://mobiliteitszentral.hafas.de/hafas/ajax-getstop.exe> or <http://travelplanner.mobiliteit.lu/hafas/ajax-getstop.exe>\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) works.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) shows to the regular version.\\n\\nThis is hilarious: <http://mobil.insa.de/> and <http://fahrinfo.insa.de/>\\n\\n## Poland\\n\\n### Bilkom\\n\\n* <http://rozklad.bilkom.pl/bin/extxml.exe>\\n* <http://rozklad.bilkom.pl/bin/query.exe>\\n* <http://rozklad.bilkom.pl/bin/stboard.exe>\\n* <http://rozklad.bilkom.pl/bin/ajax-getstop.exe>\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) works.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) works.\\n\\n### PKP\\n\\nSee <https://gist.github.com/anonymous/2fd097e38ad778ed6d457253e19bd060> for more details.\\n\\n## Sweden\\n\\n### Samtrafiken\\n\\n* <http://reseplanerare.resrobot.se/bin/extxml.exe>\\n* <http://reseplanerare.resrobot.se/bin/query.exe>, redirects to <http://reseplanerare.resrobot.se/bin/help.exe?tpl=webapp>\\n* <http://reseplanerare.resrobot.se/bin/stboard.exe>\\n* <http://reseplanerare.resrobot.se/bin/ajax-getstop.exe>\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) doesn''t work, but regular version is responsive.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) doesn''t work.\\n\\n## Switzerland\\n\\n### SBB\\n\\n* <http://fahrplan.sbb.ch/bin/extxml.exe>\\n* <http://fahrplan.sbb.ch/bin/query.exe>\\n* <http://fahrplan.sbb.ch/bin/stboard.exe>\\n* <http://fahrplan.sbb.ch/bin/ajax-getstop.exe>\\n* <http://fahrplan.sbb.ch/bin/help.exe/dn?tpl=showmap%5Fexternal> (live map, old ui)\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) works.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) shows the regular version.\\n\\n### TPG (Genf)\\n\\n* <http://tpg.hafas.de/hafas/tp/query.exe>\\n* <http://tpg.hafas.de/hafas/tp/stboard.exe>\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) doesn''t work.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) works.\\n\\n### ZVV (Zrich)\\n\\n* <http://online.fahrplan.zvv.ch/bin/ajax-getstop.exe>\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) works.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) shows the regular version.\\n\\nWhat a beautiful interface! Responsive and map-based!\\n\\n## United States of America\\n\\n### SEPTA (Pennsylvania)\\n\\n* <http://airs1.septa.org/bin/extxml.exe>\\n* <http://airs1.septa.org/bin/query.exe>\\n* <http://airs1.septa.org/bin/stboard.exe>\\n* <http://airs1.septa.org/bin/ajax-getstop.exe>\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) doesn''t work.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) works, but isn''t really text-based.\\n\\n## Defunct\\n\\n### Kombinierter Fhr- und Autoroutenplaner\\n\\nFerry routing, operated from 2006 to 2010.\\n\\n* <http://ferry-routing.com/bin/query.exe>\\n* <http://ferry-routing.com/bin/stboard.exe>\\n\\nRegular version (`/en`) works.\\n\\nMobile version (`/eox`) doesn''t work.\\n\\nText version (`/el`) works.\\n\\n## more stuff\\n\\n* <http://innovation2015.hafas.de/bin/help.exe/dn?tpl=webapp>\\n* <http://www.expressbussguiden.se/bin/help.exe/en?L=vs%5Flivemap&tpl=fullscreenmap>\\n\\n@norpol \\n\\n Copy link \\n\\n### \\n\\n**norpol**  commented Jun 6, 2018 \\n\\nAustria/Vienna <https://anachb.at> <https://anachb.vor.at/bin/mgate.exe>\\n\\n Sorry, something went wrong.\\n\\n@0bmxa \\n\\n Copy link \\n\\n### \\n\\n**0bmxa**  commented Feb 5, 2019  \\n\\n edited \\n\\nLoading \\n\\nOne more for Poland: <http://mobil.rozklad-pkp.pl/bin/query.exe> (also at <http://old.rozklad-pkp.pl/bin/query.exe> )  \\nAnd Warsaw''s ZTM: <http://wyszukiwarka.ztm.waw.pl/bin/query.exe>\\n\\n Sorry, something went wrong.\\n\\n@muekoeff \\n\\n Copy link \\n\\n### \\n\\n**muekoeff**  commented Apr 22, 2019 \\n\\nFound an official API documentation from 2015 by HaCon published by the German Ministry of Traffic BMVI.\\n\\n Sorry, something went wrong.\\n\\n@derhuerst \\n\\n Copy link \\n\\nAuthor \\n\\n### \\n\\n**derhuerst**  commented Jun 29, 2020 \\n\\n> Found an official API documentation from 2015 by HaCon published by the German Ministry of Traffic BMVI.\\n\\nKeep in mind that this documentation is for the `rest.exe` HAFAS APIs.                       |                                                                                      |                     |                  |\\n\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n* README\\n* ISC license\\n\\n# oebb\\n\\nClient for the Austrian Federal Railways (BB) API. Inofficial, using endpoints by _BB_. Ask them for permission before using this module in production. **Actually, there should be no need for projects like this since endpoints for state-owned public transportation operators should be open to the public. It''s ~~2017, 2018, 2019,~~ 2020\\\\. By the way: Even Deutsche Bahn gets this now, and you don''t ever want to be less progressive than them, because that would hurt their pride .**\\n\\nThis module conforms to the FPTI-JS 0.3.2 standard for JavaScript public transportation modules.\\n\\nnpm version Build Status license fpti-js version\\n\\n## Installation\\n\\nnpm install oebb\\n\\n## Usage\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb'')\\n\\nThe `oebb` module conforms to the FPTI-JS 0.3.2 standard for JavaScript public transportation modules and exposes the following methods:\\n\\n| Method                                                                    | Feature description         | [FPTI-JS 0.3.2](https://github.com/public-transport/fpti-js/tree/0.3.2)                               |\\n| ------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| [stations.search(query, \\\\[opt\\\\])](#stationssearchquery-opt)               | Search stations by _query_. | [ yes](https://github.com/public-transport/fpti-js/blob/0.3.2/docs/stations-stops-regions.search.md) |\\n| [journeys(origin, destination, \\\\[opt\\\\])](#journeysorigin-destination-opt) | Journeys between stations   | [ yes](https://github.com/public-transport/fpti-js/blob/0.3.2/docs/journeys.md)                      |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `stations.search(query, [opt])`\\n\\nSearch stations by _query_. See this method in the FPTI-JS 0.3.2 spec.\\n\\n#### Supported Options\\n\\n| Attribute | Description                     | FPTI-spec | Value type | Default |\\n| --------- | ------------------------------- | --------- | ---------- | ------- |\\n| results   | Max. number of results returned |          | Number     | null    |\\n\\n#### Example\\n\\noebb.stations.search(''Wie'', { results: 2 }).then()\\n\\n[\\n\\t\\t{\\n\\t\\t\\ttype: ''station'',\\n\\t\\t\\tid: ''1190100'',\\n\\t\\t\\tname: ''Wien'',\\n\\t\\t\\tmeta: true, // indicates that this is a \\\"meta\\\" station, actually representing a group of stations, corresponding to the city of vienna in this case\\n\\t\\t\\tlocation: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''location'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlongitude: 16.372134,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlatitude: 48.208547\\n\\t\\t\\t}\\n\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t{\\n\\t\\t\\ttype: ''station'',\\n\\t\\t\\tid: ''1290401'',\\n\\t\\t\\tname: ''Wien Hbf (U)'',\\n\\t\\t\\tmeta: false,\\n\\t\\t\\tlocation: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''location'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlongitude: 16.375326,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tlatitude: 48.185507\\n\\t\\t\\t}\\n\\t\\t}\\n\\t]\\n\\n---\\n\\n### `journeys(origin, destination, [opt])`\\n\\nFind journeys between stations. See this method in the FPTI-JS 0.3.2 spec.\\n\\n#### Supported Options\\n\\n| Attribute      | Description                                                                   | FPTI-spec | Value type                                                                                      | Default    |\\n| -------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------- |\\n| when           | Journey date, synonym to departureAfter                                       |          | [Date](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global%5FObjects/date) | new Date() |\\n| departureAfter | List journeys with a departure (first leg) after this date                    |          | [Date](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global%5FObjects/date) | new Date() |\\n| results        | Max. number of results returned                                               |          | Number                                                                                          | null       |\\n| interval       | Results for how many minutes after when/departureAfter                        |          | Number                                                                                          | null       |\\n| transfers      | Max. number of transfers                                                      |          | Number                                                                                          | null       |\\n| prices         | Add price information to journeys (spawning an additional request internally) |          | Boolean                                                                                         | true       |\\n\\n#### Example\\n\\nconst berlin = ''8011160'' // station id\\nconst vienna = { // FPTF station\\n    type: ''station'',\\n    id: ''1190100'',\\n    name: ''Wien''\\n    // \\n}\\n\\noebb.journeys(berlin, vienna, { when: new Date(''2019-11-02T05:00:00+02:00''), results: 1 }).then()\\n\\n[\\n\\t{\\n\\t\\ttype: ''journey'',\\n\\t\\tid: ''fb829242f221c309fb7fecf4fe87a7e169c084b23274d3c1d1f1a1ce2aed040b'',\\n\\t\\tlegs: [\\n\\t\\t\\t{\\n\\t\\t\\t\\torigin: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''station'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tid: ''8098160'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''Berlin Hbf (tief)''\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tdestination: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''station'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tid: ''8010205'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''Leipzig Hbf''\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tdeparture: ''2019-11-02T04:28:00+01:00'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tdeparturePlatform: ''2'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tarrival: ''2019-11-02T05:42:00+01:00'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tarrivalPlatform: ''12'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\thasRealtimeInformation: false,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tline: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''line'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tid: ''ICE 501'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''ICE 501'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tnumber: ''501'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tproduct: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''ICE'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tshortName: ''ICE'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tlongName: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tde: ''Intercity Express'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ten: ''Intercity Express'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tit: ''Intercity express''\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t}\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tmode: ''train'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tpublic: true,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\toperator: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''https://www.oebb.at/''\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t}\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tmode: ''train'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\tpublic: true,\\n\\t\\t\\t\\toperator: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''https://www.oebb.at/''\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t}\\n\\t\\t\\t},\\n\\t\\t\\t{\\n\\t\\t\\t\\torigin: {\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\ttype: ''station'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tid: ''8010205'',\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tname: ''Leipzig    |\\n\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n* README\\n* MIT license\\n\\n# BB API Documentation\\n\\nInoffical documentation for common API endpoints of the Austrian Federal Railways (BB), which are used on <https://tickets.oebb.at> (and probably in the mobile apps as well).\\n\\nI ignored most of the optional parameters, headers etc. to provide the simpliest way of usage.\\n\\n## Usage\\n\\n### Connections between stations\\n\\n1. Authentication\\n2. Find Stations for start and destination\\n3. Find Connections between the stations\\n\\n## Further APIs\\n\\nThe are many additional APIs like:\\n\\n* Departures and Arrivals at a specific station\\n* \\\"Zug Radar\\\" - Live Positions of Trains\\n\\nIn case someones needs them, feel free to create a PR or an issue.\\n\\n## Client Libraries\\n\\n* NodeJS: <https://github.com/juliuste/oebb> (base for this documentation, thanks!)\\n\\n##
