         |                  |\\n| [package.json](/mymro/oebb-api/blob/master/package.json \\\"package.json\\\")                | [package.json](/mymro/oebb-api/blob/master/package.json \\\"package.json\\\")                |                     |                  |\\n| View all files                                                                         |                                                                                        |                     |                  |\\n\\n## Repository files navigation\\n\\n* README\\n\\n# OEBB-API (BB-API)\\n\\nA collection of functions fore node.js to acess train shedules, arrivals/departures, station search and ticketinformation from the OEBB(BB)\\n\\nI had a lot of help help from these great ressources\\n\\n* HAFAS Fahrplanauskunft API - Sammlung\\n* Austrian Federal Railways (BB) API client by juliuste\\n\\nand a documentation file I found on the web\\n\\n## Installation\\n\\nnpm --save install oebb-api\\n\\n## Functions\\n\\n* searchStationsNew\\n* searchStations\\n* getJourneys\\n* getStationBoardData\\n* getStationBoardDataOptions\\n* getStationSearchOptions\\n\\n### searchStationsNew(name)\\n\\nIt returns an promise that resolves to an array of possible stations matching `name`\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n\\noebb.searchStationsNew(\\\"Wien\\\").then(console.log);\\n\\nreturns\\n\\n[{ number: 1190100,\\n    longitude: 16372134,\\n    latitude: 48208547,\\n    name: '''',\\n    meta: ''Wien'' },\\n  { number: 1290401,\\n    longitude: 16375326,\\n    latitude: 48185507,\\n    name: ''Wien Hbf (U)'',\\n    meta: '''' },\\n...\\n...\\n...]\\n\\n### searchStations(options)\\n\\n_searchStation_ is very similar to _searchStationsNew_ it however can take more options and returns more information. You can call getStationSearchOptions to get a prefilled options object.\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n\\nvar options = oebb.getStationSearchOptions();\\noptions.S=\\\"wien h\\\";\\noebb.searchStations(options).then(console.log);\\n\\nIt returns an array with matching stations, POIs, etc.\\n\\n[ { value: ''Wien Hbf (U)'',\\n    id: ''A=1@O=Wien Hbf (U)@X=16375326@Y=48185507@U=181@L=001290401@B=1@p=1513853468@'',\\n    extId: ''001290401'',\\n    type: ''1'',\\n    typeStr: ''[Bhf/Hst]'',\\n    xcoord: ''16375326'',\\n    ycoord: ''48185507'',\\n    state: ''id'',\\n    prodClass: ''6013'',\\n    weight: ''32767'' },\\n  { value: ''Wien Meidling'',\\n    id: ''A=1@O=Wien Meidling@X=16333211@Y=48174559@U=181@L=001191201@B=1@p=1513853468@'',\\n    extId: ''001191201'',\\n    type: ''1'',\\n    typeStr: ''[Bhf/Hst]'',\\n    xcoord: ''16333211'',\\n    ycoord: ''48174559'',\\n    state: ''id'',\\n    prodClass: ''4989'',\\n    weight: ''32588'' },\\n...\\n...\\n...]\\n\\n| Name      | description                                                                                     |\\n| --------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| value:    | name of the station                                                                             |\\n| id        | no idea                                                                                         |\\n| extId     | used in other queries; same as number (not quite shure if the really are the same all the time) |\\n| type      | int representing the type                                                                       |\\n| typeStr   | the type as string                                                                              |\\n| xcoord    | longitude                                                                                       |\\n| ycoord    | latitude                                                                                        |\\n| state     | no idea                                                                                         |\\n| prodClass | no idea                                                                                         |\\n| weight    | I am guessing it represents how close a match the station is to the string                      |\\n\\n### getStationSearchOptions()\\n\\nIt returns an object containing the options for searchStations\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n\\nvar options = oebb.getStationSearchOptions();\\n\\n#### options\\n\\n| Name                | default value | value                     | description                                                    |\\n| ------------------- | ------------- | ------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| REQ0JourneyStopsS0A | 1             | An int between 1 and 255. | It selects the type of station to return e.g. 1 is \\\\[Bhf/Hst\\\\] |\\n| REQ0JourneyStopsB   | 12            | An int greater 0          | the amount of results which are returned                       |\\n| S                   | a string      | the string to match       |                                                                |\\n| js                  | true          | boolean                   | no idea what it does                                           |\\n\\n### getStationBoardData(options)\\n\\nIt returns a promise resolving to an object containing arrival or depature information for a specific station. You can get a prefilled options object, by calling getStationBoardDataOptions\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n\\nvar options = oebb.getStationBoardDataOptions();\\noptions.evaId=1191601;//Ottakring (Wien)\\noebb.getStationBoardData(options).then(console.log);\\n\\nreturns:\\n\\n{ headTexts:\\n   [ ''Zeit'',\\n     ''Fahrt'',\\n     ''Nach'',\\n     ''Steig'',\\n     ''Abfahrten'',\\n     ''Aktuell'',\\n     ''Ankunft'' ],\\n  stationName: ''Ottakring (Wien)'',\\n  stationEvaId: ''1191601'',\\n  boardType: ''dep'',\\n  imgPath: ''/img/'',\\n  iconProductsSubPath: ''vs_oebb/'',\\n  rtInfo: true,\\n  journey:\\n   [ { id: ''875171810'',\\n       ti: ''19:46'',\\n       da: ''23.12.2017'',\\n       pr: ''U3'',\\n       st: ''Wien Simmering'',\\n       lastStop: ''Wien Simmering Bahnhof (U3)'',\\n       ati: ''20:12'',\\n       tr: ''1'',\\n       trChg: false,\\n       rt: false,\\n       rta: false },\\n     { id: ''836641815'',\\n       ti: ''19:46'',\\n       da: ''23.12.2017'',\\n       pr: ''Tram 46'',\\n       st: ''Wien Ring/Volkstheater U'',\\n       lastStop: ''Wien Dr.-K.-Renner-Ring/Volkstheater (Schleife)'',\\n       ati: ''20:00'',\\n       tr: '''',\\n       trChg: ,\\n       rt: { status: null, dlm: ''2'', dlt: ''19:47'' , dld:''23.12.2017''},\\n       rta: false },\\n       ...\\n       ...\\n       ...\\n ],\\n  maxJ: 18 }\\n\\n#### element description\\n\\n##### general:\\n\\n| Name                | description                            |\\n| ------------------- | -------------------------------------- |\\n| headTexts           | headings for arrivals depatures screen |\\n| stationName         | name of station                        |\\n| stationEvaId        | Id of station                          |\\n| boardType           | depatures or arrivals (dep/arr)        |\\n| imgPath             | ?                                      |\\n| iconProductsSubPath | ?                                      |\\n| rtInfo              | ?                                      |\\n| maxJ                | number of returned entries -1          |\\n\\n##### journey:\\n\\n| Name     | description                                                                                   |\\n| -------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| id       | ?                                                                                             |\\n| ti       | arrvial/depature time                                                                         |\\n| da       | arrival/depature date                                                                         |\\n| pr       | name of transport                                                                             |\\n| st       | ?                                                                                             |\\n| lastStop | last stop                                                                                     |\\n| ati      | wehn arrivals depature time from first stop ; when depatures expected time to reach last stop |\\n| tr       | track identifier                                                                              |\\n| trChg    | did the track change                                                                          |\\n\\n##### rt :\\n\\nit describes the delay or other status if there is one. If there is one it contains an object formated as follows:\\n\\n| Name   | description                           |\\n| ------ | ------------------------------------- |\\n| status | current status; \\\"Ausfall\\\" if canceled |\\n| dlm    | how many minutes too late             |\\n| dlt    | actual arrival time                   |\\n| dld    | actual arrival date                   |\\n\\n##### rta\\n\\nit is very similar to rt I think it describes the delay for the arrival, but I am not certain.\\n\\n| Name   | description                                                                          |\\n| ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\\n| status | current status \\\"Ausfall\\\" if canceled then rt too is canceld and rt.status= \\\"Ausfall\\\" |\\n| dlm    | never seen it other than empty                                                       |\\n| dlt    | never seen it other than empty                                                       |\\n\\n### getStationBoardDataOptions()\\n\\nreturns prefilled options for getStationBoardData\\n\\nconst oebb = require(''oebb-api'');\\n\\nvar options = oebb.getStationBoardDataOptions();\\n\\n#### options\\n\\n| Name           | default value             | values                    | description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |\\n| -------------- | ------------------------- | ------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\\n| L              | vs\\\\_scotty.vs\\\\_liveticker | vs\\\\_scotty.vs\\\\_liveticker | ?            method: \"GET\",\n            json: true,\n            headers: { Channel: \"inet\" },\n            qs: { userId: userId },\n            timeout: 10000\n        }, (error, response, body) OEBB API Direct Client\n\nThis is a modern JavaScript client for the Austrian Federal Railways (BB) API, created to replace the outdated oebb-api npm package.\n\n## Background\n\nThe original [oebb-api](https://github.com/mymro/oebb-api) npm package is no longer maintained (last updated in 2017) and has compatibility issues with the current OEBB API. This project provides a modern ES module alternative that works with the current API.\n\n## Features\n\n- Search for train stations by name\n- Get live train departures from a station\n- Check for train delays and cancellations\n- Modern ES module syntax\n- Promise-based API\n- Works with current BB API (as of May 2025)\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install request\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n### Station Search\n\n```javascript\nimport { searchStations } from ''./oebb-direct.js'';\n\n// Search for stations matching \"Wien\"\nsearchStations(''Wien'')\n  .then(stations => {\n    console.log(''Found stations:'', stations);\n    // stations contains array of objects with station details\n  })\n  .catch(error => {\n    console.error(''Error:'', error);\n  });\n```\n\n### Train Departures\n\n```javascript\nimport { getTrainDepartures } from ''./oebb-direct.js'';\n\n// Get departures from Wien Hauptbahnhof (station ID: 1290401)\ngetTrainDepartures(''1290401'')\n  .then(departures => {\n    // Process train departures\n    departures.forEach(train => {\n      const hasDelay = train.rt && train.rt.dlm;\n      console.log(`${train.pr} to ${train.lastStop}: ${train.ti} ${hasDelay ? `(Delayed by ${train.rt.dlm} min)` : ''(On time)''}`);\n    });\n  })\n  .catch(error => {\n    console.error(''Error:'', error);\n  });\n```\n\n### Check Train Delay\n\n```javascript\nimport { checkTrainDelay } from ''./oebb-direct.js'';\n\n// Check if RJ 373 is delayed at Wien Hauptbahnhof (station ID: 1290401)\ncheckTrainDelay(''1290401'', ''RJ 373'')\n  .then(result => {\n    if (result.canceled) {\n      console.log(''Train is canceled'');\n    } else if (result.isDelayed) {\n      console.log(`Train is delayed by ${result.delayMinutes} minutes`);\n      console.log(`Scheduled: ${result.scheduledDeparture}`);\n      console.log(`Actual: ${result.actualDeparture}`);\n    } else {\n      console.log(''Train is on time'');\n    }\n  })\n  .catch(error => {\n    console.error(''Error:'', error);\n  });\n```\n\n## Command Line Interface\n\nA command-line demo script is included for quick testing:\n\n```bash\n# Search for stations\nnode demo.js search Wien\n\n# Get departures from a station\nnode demo.js departures 1290401\n\n# Check if a specific train is delayed\nnode demo.js delay 1290401 \"RJ 373\"\n```\n\n## API Documentation\n\n### searchStations(name, count = 15)\n\nSearches for stations matching the given name.\n\n- **name** (string): Station name to search for\n- **count** (number, optional): Maximum number of results to return (default: 15)\n- **returns**: Promise resolving to an array of station objects\n\n### getTrainDepartures(stationId, date = new Date())\n\nGets train departures from a specific station.\n\n- **stationId** (string): The station ID\n- **date** (Date, optional): Date for departures (default: current time)\n- **returns**: Promise resolving to an array of departure objects\n\n### checkTrainDelay(stationId, trainNumber)\n\nChecks if a specific train is delayed at a station.\n\n- **stationId** (string): The station ID\n- **trainNumber** (string): The train number (e.g., \"RJ 373\")\n- **returns**: Promise resolving to an object with delay information\n\n## Data Structure\n\n### Station Object\n\n```javascript\n{\n  number: \"1290401\",          // Station ID\n                   // Additional information\n}\n```\n\n### Train Departure Object\n\n```javascript\n{\n  id: \"110842810\",            // Internal ID\n  ti: \"20:58\",                // Scheduled departure time\n  da: \"07.05.2025\",           // Departure date\n  pr: \"RJ 373\",               // Train name/number\n  st: \"Graz Hbf\",             // Destination name\n  lastStop: \"Graz Hbf\",                    // Realtime information (if delayed)\n    status: null,             // Status (null or \"Ausfall\" for canceled)\n    dlm: \"25\",                // Delay in minutes\n    dlt: \"21:23\",             // Actual departure time\n    dld: \"07.05.2025\"         // Actual departure date\n  },\n  rta: false                  // Additional realtime flag\n}\n```\n\n## Notes\n\nThis for train delays and cancellations\\n- Modern ES module syntax\\n- Promise-based API\\n- Works with current BB API (as of May 2025)\\n\\n## Installation\\n\\n```bash\\nnpm install request\\n```\\n\\n## Usage\\n\\n### Station Search\\n\\n```javascript\\nimport { searchStations } from ''./oebb-direct.js'';\\n\\n// Search for stations matching @returns {Promise<Array>} - Array of station status objects\n */\nexport function trackTrainJourney(trainName, stationIds) {\n    // Use the authentication once for all stations\n    return authenticate()\n        .then(auth => {\n            // Create an array of promises for each station check\n            const stationPromises = stationIds.map(stationId => {\n                return getBoardData(auth, stationId)\n                    .then(departures => {\n                        // Try to find the train at this station\n                        const train = departures.find(d => {\n                            const fullName = (d.pr || '''').toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, '''');\n                            return fullName === trainName.toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, '''') || \n                                   d.pr === trainName ||\n                                   (d.pr && d.pr.toLowerCase().includes(trainName.toLowerCase()));\n                        });\n                 stationId,\n                                found: false,\n                                status: ''not_found''\n                            };\n                        }\n                        \n                        // Check if the train has already departed from this station\n                        const now = new Date();\n                        const scheduledTime = Last seen at ${lastDeparted.stationId}`);\n          }\n        } else if (nextArrival) {\n          console.log(`- Has not yet departed from first station (${nextArrival.stationId})`);\n
